      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BADGER'S BEAST (8) was a last start winner (25.09) at this track who is building a strong winning record. Form at this distance is sound. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Hard to fault his form and makes plenty of appeal again. MCKEON (3) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind BADGER'S BEAST (25.19) in a NG. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. Will give a great sight again. TERESITA (1) boxed on well to finish third last time, beaten 2 lengths (25.52) behind DRINK TINS at this track. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Can feature again. BENTLEY OLAF (2) looks an each-way chance.",
